HONG KONG , October 1 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- About 5,000 Hong Kong citizens visited barracks of the Garrison of the Chinese People 's Liberation Army -LRB- PLA -RRB- in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region -LRB- SAR -RRB- today , the National Day , as the military sites were opened for local residents for the first time .
The citizens from 108 organizations visited the gunboats at the Stonecutters Island naval base and toured the camps at the Stanley barracks .
They watched cultural shows , military exhibitions and soccer matches during the first open day .
This was the first time since Hong Kong 's return to the motherland on July 1 that local residents have been allowed inside the garrison 's military bases and also marked the first National Day celebrations by PLA forces in Hong Kong SAR .
